@namespace DotNetCloud.Modules.Photos.UI

@*
    Help content for the Photos module.
*@

<div class="help-content">
    <section class="help-section">
        <h2 class="help-section-title">Overview</h2>
        <p>DotNetCloud Photos lets you upload, organize, view, and share your photos. Browse your collection in a beautiful gallery interface with album organization.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="help-section">
        <h2 class="help-section-title">Uploading Photos</h2>
        <p>Click the <strong>Upload</strong> button or drag and drop photos directly onto the page. Supported formats include JPEG, PNG, WebP, and HEIC. Photos are automatically organized by date.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="help-section">
        <h2 class="help-section-title">Browsing Photos</h2>
        <p><strong>Gallery view:</strong> Browse all your photos in a responsive grid layout with thumbnails.</p>
        <p><strong>Albums:</strong> Create albums to group photos by event, trip, or category. Add photos to multiple albums without duplication.</p>
        <p><strong>Timeline:</strong> View photos organized chronologically, grouped by year and month.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="help-section">
        <h2 class="help-section-title">Viewing Photos</h2>
        <p>Click a photo to open the lightbox viewer. Navigate between photos with arrow keys or on-screen controls. View photo details including date, resolution, and file size.</p>
        <p><strong>Slideshow:</strong> Start a fullscreen slideshow to automatically advance through your photos.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="help-section">
        <h2 class="help-section-title">Sharing</h2>
        <p>Share individual photos or entire albums with other users or via shareable links.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="help-section">
        <h2 class="help-section-title">Tips &amp; Tricks</h2>
        <ul class="help-tips">
            <li>Use albums to organize photos from specific events or trips.</li>
            <li>The timeline view is great for finding photos from a particular date range.</li>
            <li>Use the search bar to find photos by filename or date.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>
</div>
